National chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Comrade Adams Oshiomhole on Saturday night congratulated the newly elected Senator, Smart Adeyemi for a “well deserved victory in the Kogi West re-run election. The APC national chairman in a statement he personally signed said the defeat of the candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Dino Melaye, ”has again affirmed the general acceptance of our great party, by the great people of Kogi State who just few weeks ago voted massively for our governorship candidate, Governor Yahaya Bello, who was re-elected for a second term.” BREAKING: Three inspectors, two police officers arrested for… Buhari’s $29.96 billion loan, plan to cripple Nigeria… Kogi West election: Gunmen arrested in Kabba Between the police and Abdullahi’s Hate Bill He further expressed his conviction ”in the ability of the people of Kogi West to elect leaders who will make them proud in the Senate and not the defeated Senator Melaye who is among the 16 Senators who rebelled against our party. ”As it stands today, the broom has swept away the entire 16 Senators, Dino being the last, who tried to destabilise our democracy for their personal interest, jettisoning the interest of the electorate. ”On behalf of our great party the APC, I congratulate my brother and friend, Senator Smart Adeyemi once again and we look forward toward working with you in this resolve by our dear President, Muhammadu Buhari to take the nation to the Next Level.” SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
